## 3. Frontend Architecture: State & Synchronization

### A. Admin Dashboard (React)
- **Component Architecture**: Modular component-based hierarchy with specialized layout containers (`AdminLayout`, [Sidebar](file:///c:/Users/admin/Desktop/Restaurant%20App/admin-dashboard/src/components/Sidebar.tsx#24-126)).
- **State Management**: React Context (`AuthContext`) for global state (user profile, token) and local state/hooks for feature-specific data.
- **Routing**: `react-router-dom` with [ProtectedRoute](file:///c:/Users/admin/Desktop/Restaurant%20App/admin-dashboard/src/App.tsx#22-36) wrappers for RBAC enforcement at the UI layer.

### B. Customer App (Flutter)
- **Reactive Pattern**: Uses `Provider` for reactive UI updates when cart or user status changes.
- **Multi-Provider Paradigm**: Decoupled providers for [Auth](file:///c:/Users/admin/Desktop/Restaurant%20App/backend/src/middlewares/authMiddleware.ts#10-13), `Cart`, `Location`, `Navigation`, and `ThemeProvider`.
- **Infrastructure Integration**: Uses `LocationProvider` for geo-fencing or address-based service logic.

